Fixing x:A, we must construct an identification from H
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen f x\right \rparen \mathclose {}
 to \mathsf {act}_{f}
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen H x\right \rparen \mathclose {}
. By the naturality (Lemma ) of H at the identification H x\colon  f x = x, we have an identification H
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen f x\right \rparen \mathclose {}
 \cdot  \mathsf {act}_{1_{A}}
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen H x\right \rparen \mathclose {}
 = \mathsf {act}_{f}
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen H x\right \rparen \mathclose {}
\cdot  H x.

Simplifying, we have H
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen f x\right \rparen \mathclose {}
\cdot  H x = \mathsf {act}_{f}
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen H x\right \rparen \mathclose {}
\cdot  H x; canceling H x on either side, we therefore have the desired identification H
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen f x\right \rparen \mathclose {}
 = \mathsf {act}_{f}
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen H x\right \rparen \mathclose {}
.

